      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint for COU2 VAD hemolysis CFD model",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model is applicable only to centrifugal blood pumps with impeller tip diameters between 25 mm and 55 mm, operating with bovine or human blood analogues at hematocrit values of 30–45%. The power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation) is valid for exposure times between 0.001 s and 1.0 s per passage and shear stresses between 50 Pa and 400 Pa. Application outside these bounds requires additional validation evidence."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
