      "description": "Flow rate: 2.0–8.0 L/min; Pump rotational speed: 2000–3500 RPM; Inlet pressure: 5–20 mmHg; Outlet pressure: 60–120 mmHg; Blood viscosity: 0.0030–0.0040 Pa·s (non-Newtonian Carreau model); Hematocrit: 30–45%; Fluid temperature: 36–38 °C; Impeller tip diameter: 38 mm (FDA generic geometry); Clearance gap: 0.3–0.5 mm. All five nominal operating points (2 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3 L/min at 2500 RPM, 4 L/min at 2500 RPM, 5 L/min at 3000 RPM, 6 L/min at 3500 RPM) lie within this envelope."
    }
